INTRUSION DETECTION SYSTEM USING SNORT
Date:


AIM
To demonstrate intrusion detection system using snort on Kali Linux by
detecting suspicious network activity and generating alerts.

ALGORITHM

STEP 1: Start Kali Linux in VMware. STEP 2: Install Snort IDS tool.
STEP 3: Configure Snort with the local network address. STEP 4: Test Snort configuration.
STEP 5: Run Snort in IDS mode. STEP 6: Create a custom IDS rule STEP 7: Generate network traffic.
STEP 8: Observe alerts generated by Snort. STEP 9: Observe alerts generated by Snort. STEP 10: Verify log files.

PROGRAM CODING:

Install Snort Command:
sudo wget https://archive.kali.org/archive-keyring.gpg -O /usr/share/keyrings/kali-archive-keyring.gpg
sudo apt update

sudo apt install snort -y
Sample Output:

Setting up snort (2.9.x) ... 
Snort successfully installed

Verify Snort Installation
Command:
snort --version

Configure Snort Command:
sudo nano /etc/snort/snort.conf
Configuration Entry:

ipvar HOME_NET 192.168.1.0/24
Sample Output:

Configuration file updated successfully


Test Snort Configuration 
Command:
sudo snort -T -c /etc/snort/snort.lua

Sample Output:

Snort successfully validated the configuration!
Run Snort in Intrusion Detection System Mode Command:
sudo snort -c /etc/snort/snort.lua -i eth0
Sample Output:
Running in IDS mode...
